      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "body": "Goal: Make large graphs load and interact without freezing\nStatus: done\n\nTasks in scope:\n1. Collapse repeated edge-layer graph scans\n2. Gate the physics loop to nav mode only\n3. Make group bounds recomputation incremental\n4. Cap history and story snapshot pressure\n5. Reduce semantic adjacency expansion cost\n6. Trim save/export pipeline churn\n\nOpen questions:\n1. Which work should move off the main thread first?",
        "status": "done",
        "owner": "Michael",
        "priority": "critical",
        "estimateHours": "3",
        "acceptanceCriteria": [
          "Edge rendering uses indexed node lookup instead of repeated array scans",
          "Obstacle geometry is computed once per draw cycle",
          "Large graphs stop paying per-edge whole-graph costs"
        ],
